  <h2>What Is a Black Diamond?</h2>
  <p>
    Black diamonds are genuine diamonds whose dense inclusions (graphite, magnetite, or numerous micro-fractures) absorb light, giving a distinctive opaque appearance. Many stones on the market are heat- or irradiation-treated to reach a deep, even black; natural black diamonds exist but are rarer and usually command higher prices.
    For background reading, see
    <a href="https://4cs.gia.edu/en-us/blog/black-diamonds-what-you-need-to-know/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">GIA: Black diamonds — what you need to know</a>.
  </p>

